                Eighthly, Conſider the great account you are ere long to give, when you muſt be called to render account of your ſtewardſhip, Luke 16. 2. when the trumpet ſhall blow, and another throne erected, and you your ſelves to be judged who of late judged others;


Nuper eram judex, jam judicis ante tribunal

Subſiſtens paveo, judicor ipſe modo.
